A software designer for time and attendance management, responsible for creating software that efficiently tracks and manages employee attendance and work hours. Key responsibilities include:

Gather and analyze user requirements for the time and attendance software.
Design software architecture and user interface to meet requirements.
Develop and implement features such as time tracking, leave management, and schedule creation.
Ensure software integration with payroll and HR systems.
Test and debug software to ensure its accuracy and stability.
Collaborate with development and testing teams to deliver a high-quality product.
Stay up-to-date with industry trends and advancements in time and attendance technology.
Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or related field.
Strong understanding of software design and development principles.
Experience in designing and developing time and attendance management systems.
Proficiency in programming languages such as Java, Python, or .NET.
Excellent communication and problem-solving skills.
